---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="The Story" description="Learn about Operation Golden Sword - the three acts of this epic DnD Day event.">
  <!-- Header -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-dnd-bg-secondary">
    <div class="container-custom text-center">
      <p class="section-title">The Campaign</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-display mb-4">
        <span class="gold-gradient">Operation Golden Sword</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="text-dnd-text-muted text-lg max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        A four-act epic where heroes must race against time to break the Iron Conclave's grip on Amn.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Setting -->
  <section class="py-16">
    <div class="container-custom">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-display text-dnd-primary mb-6">The Setting</h2>

        <div class="space-y-4 text-dnd-text-muted leading-relaxed">
          <p>
            <strong class="text-dnd-text">Location:</strong> The Sword Coast
          </p>
          <p>
            <strong class="text-dnd-text">Primary Objective:</strong> The coastal region of the Kingdom of Amn
          </p>
          <p>
            The Kingdom of Amn ‚Äî one of the wealthiest powers on the Sword Coast ‚Äî has fallen.
            Its capital city, <strong class="text-dnd-text">Athkatla</strong>, has been enslaved by
            <a href="/enemies" class="text-dnd-secondary hover:text-dnd-primary transition-colors font-semibold">High Forgemaster Thar√ªm Blackmantle</a> and his <a href="/enemies" class="text-dnd-secondary hover:text-dnd-primary transition-colors font-semibold">Iron Conclave</a>.
          </p>
          <p>
            Massive armies now guard every land approach into the kingdom, forming an impenetrable wall of
            steel, siegecraft, and merciless discipline.
          </p>
          <p>
            The coastline, however ‚Äî though heavily fortified ‚Äî remains the only viable weakness. It is the fastest
            route inland, and the only path that can bypass the Conclave's land armies before they fully mobilize.
          </p>
          <p class="text-dnd-primary font-semibold">
            This vulnerability has drawn a desperate gamble: a full-scale amphibious invasion.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- True Objective -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-dnd-bg-secondary">
    <div class="container-custom">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-display text-dnd-primary mb-6">The True Objective</h2>

        <p class="text-dnd-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-6">
          The goal of DnD Day is not to reclaim Amn in a single battle.
          <strong class="text-dnd-text">The goal is to capture the Coastal Keep.</strong>
        </p>

        <div class="card mb-6">
          <h3 class="font-display text-xl text-dnd-text mb-4">The Coastal Keep is:</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-dnd-text-muted">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-dnd-primary">‚Ä¢</span>
              <span>A fortress</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-dnd-primary">‚Ä¢</span>
              <span>A command hub</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-dnd-primary">‚Ä¢</span>
              <span>The primary logistical and arcane relay between Athkatla and the Iron Conclave's eastern armies</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
          <div class="card border-dnd-accent">
            <h4 class="font-display text-dnd-accent mb-3">If the Keep Falls:</h4>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-dnd-text-muted text-sm">
              <li>‚Ä¢ Eastern armies are cut off from command</li>
              <li>‚Ä¢ Reinforcements cannot be coordinated</li>
              <li>‚Ä¢ Battlefield intelligence collapses</li>
              <li>‚Ä¢ Athkatla becomes exposed</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="card border-dnd-secondary">
            <h4 class="font-display text-dnd-secondary mb-3">If the Keep Holds:</h4>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-dnd-text-muted text-sm">
              <li>‚Ä¢ The invasion will be crushed between converging armies</li>
              <li>‚Ä¢ The Iron Conclave will respond with forces too vast to resist</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <p class="text-dnd-primary font-display text-xl text-center mt-8">
          The adventurers do not need to win the war today. They only need to break it.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Act I -->
  <section class="py-16" id="act-1">
    <div class="container-custom">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-6">
          <span class="text-4xl">üè∞</span>
          <div>
            <p class="section-title">Act I</p>
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-display">The Eve of War</h2>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="card mb-6">
          <p class="text-dnd-primary text-sm uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">Location</p>
          <p class="text-dnd-text font-display text-lg">Velen, Dragon's Head Peninsula</p>
          <p class="text-dnd-text-muted text-sm mt-2 italic">Tone: Tense, anticipatory, grim camaraderie</p>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-4 text-dnd-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-8">
          <p>
            The adventurers have gathered in <strong class="text-dnd-text">Velen</strong>, a fortified coastal town
            at the tip of the Dragon's Head Peninsula. Once a bustling port town supporting Amnian trade,
            Velen now serves as the final staging ground for the invasion.
          </p>
          <p>The town is overcrowded and strained:</p>
          <ul class="space-y-2 ml-4">
            <li>‚Ä¢ Docks packed with rowboats, transport barges, and hastily reinforced vessels</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ Soldiers and mercenaries sleeping in streets and taverns</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ Signal towers manned day and night</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ The sea watched constantly for signs of movement</li>
          </ul>
          <p>Across the water, somewhere beyond the horizon, the Iron Conclave waits.</p>
        </div>

        <h3 class="font-display text-xl text-dnd-primary mb-4">Purpose of Act I</h3>
        <p class="text-dnd-text-muted mb-6">
          Act I is not about action ‚Äî it is about <strong class="text-dnd-text">weight</strong>.
          This act should let players prepare mechanically (gear, spells, consumables) and emotionally
          (farewells, vows, fear). It establishes the scale of the invasion and makes clear that
          not everyone here will survive.
        </p>

        <h3 class="font-display text-xl text-dnd-primary mb-4">Key Events</h3>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div class="card">
            <h4 class="font-display text-dnd-text mb-2">1. Final Preparations</h4>
            <p class="text-dnd-text-muted text-sm">
              Players are given limited time to spend gold, trade supplies, finalize plans, and say goodbyes.
              <strong class="text-dnd-primary">Once the invasion begins, there is no returning to Velen.</strong>
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <h4 class="font-display text-dnd-text mb-2">2. The War Council</h4>
            <p class="text-dnd-text-muted text-sm">
              All adventurers gather to hear the overarching plan. The briefing outlines the goal: seize the coast quickly.
              Forces will be split into separate theaters, and success in one area affects all others.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <h4 class="font-display text-dnd-text mb-2">3. Deployment</h4>
            <p class="text-dnd-text-muted text-sm">
              As dawn approaches, beach assault teams board landing craft, air units prepare mounts,
              infiltration forces ready teleportation circles. Horns sound across Velen. Signal fires ignite.
              <strong class="text-dnd-primary">The sea is no longer empty.</strong>
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Act II -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-dnd-bg-secondary" id="act-2">
    <div class="container-custom">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-6">
          <span class="text-4xl">‚öîÔ∏è</span>
          <div>
            <p class="section-title">Act II</p>
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-display">The Iron Tide</h2>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="card mb-6">
          <p class="text-dnd-primary text-sm uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">The Invasion</p>
          <p class="text-dnd-text-muted text-sm italic">Tone: Chaotic, heroic, overwhelming</p>
        </div>

        <p class="text-dnd-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-8">
          The heroes are split into <strong class="text-dnd-text">four theaters of war</strong>,
          each critical to the battle. No theater stands alone ‚Äî success or failure in one directly
          impacts the others.
        </p>

        <div class="grid gap-4 mb-8">
          <a href="/theaters/beach-assault" class="card border-l-4 border-theater-assault hover:border-theater-assault/80 group">
            <h4 class="font-display text-dnd-text group-hover:text-dnd-primary transition-colors">Theater 1: Beach Landing (General Assault)</h4>
            <p class="text-dnd-text-muted text-sm">Shock force and distraction ‚Äî brutal, relentless, high casualties</p>
          </a>
          <a href="/theaters/siege-train" class="card border-l-4 border-theater-siege hover:border-theater-siege/80 group">
            <h4 class="font-display text-dnd-text group-hover:text-dnd-primary transition-colors">Theater 2: Beach Landing (Siege Train)</h4>
            <p class="text-dnd-text-muted text-sm">Strategic enablers ‚Äî precision under fire</p>
          </a>
          <a href="/theaters/portals-bridges" class="card border-l-4 border-theater-portals hover:border-theater-portals/80 group">
            <h4 class="font-display text-dnd-text group-hover:text-dnd-primary transition-colors">Theater 3: Portals & Bridges</h4>
            <p class="text-dnd-text-muted text-sm">Force multiplier ‚Äî surgical, tense, isolated</p>
          </a>
          <a href="/theaters/air-battle" class="card border-l-4 border-theater-air hover:border-theater-air/80 group">
            <h4 class="font-display text-dnd-text group-hover:text-dnd-primary transition-colors">Theater 4: Air Battle (Sky Control)</h4>
            <p class="text-dnd-text-muted text-sm">Air superiority ‚Äî fast, dangerous, cinematic</p>
          </a>
        </div>

        <h3 class="font-display text-xl text-dnd-primary mb-4">How It All Connects</h3>
        <div class="card overflow-x-auto">
          <table class="w-full text-sm">
            <thead>
              <tr class="border-b border-dnd-border">
                <th class="text-left py-2 text-dnd-text font-display">Theater</th>
                <th class="text-left py-2 text-dnd-accent font-display">Helps</th>
                <th class="text-left py-2 text-dnd-secondary font-display">Hurts (if fails)</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody class="text-dnd-text-muted">
              <tr class="border-b border-dnd-border/50">
                <td class="py-2">T1 - General Assault</td>
                <td class="py-2">T2, Act III</td>
                <td class="py-2">All</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-dnd-border/50">
                <td class="py-2">T2 - Siege</td>
                <td class="py-2">Act IV</td>
                <td class="py-2">Act IV</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-dnd-border/50">
                <td class="py-2">T3 - Portals</td>
                <td class="py-2">Act III (Bridge)</td>
                <td class="py-2">Act III, T1, T2</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="py-2">T4 - Air</td>
                <td class="py-2">Act III (Bridge)</td>
                <td class="py-2">All</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <div class="text-center mt-8">
          <a href="/theaters" class="btn btn-secondary">
            Explore All Theaters in Detail
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Act III -->
  <section class="py-16" id="act-3">
    <div class="container-custom">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-6">
          <span class="text-4xl">üåâ</span>
          <div>
            <p class="section-title">Act III</p>
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-display">The Bridge</h2>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="card mb-6">
          <p class="text-dnd-primary text-sm uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">The Critical Crossing</p>
          <p class="text-dnd-text-muted text-sm italic">Tone: Tense, desperate, against the clock</p>
        </div>

        <p class="text-dnd-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-8">
          Between the beaches and the Coastal Keep lies <strong class="text-dnd-text">Pegasus Bridge</strong>
          over the Orn River ‚Äî the only crossing capable of supporting siege engines and massed troops. Intelligence confirms
          the Iron Conclave has rigged it for demolition. All four theaters must converge on this single objective.
        </p>

        <h3 class="font-display text-xl text-dnd-primary mb-4">Four Theaters, One Objective</h3>
        <p class="text-dnd-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-6">
          If the bridge falls, the invasion stalls. Every theater has a critical role to play in securing the crossing.
        </p>

        <div class="grid gap-4 mb-8">
          <div class="card border-l-4 border-theater-assault">
            <h4 class="font-display text-dnd-text mb-2">Theater 1: Gold Beach ‚Äî Break the Line</h4>
            <p class="text-dnd-text-muted text-sm mb-3">
              The assault force must smash through the entrenched enemy defensive line blocking the road
              to the bridge.
            </p>
            <ul class="text-dnd-text-muted text-sm space-y-1">
              <li>‚Ä¢ Breach fortified enemy positions between the beach and the river</li>
              <li>‚Ä¢ Clear the road for the siege train following behind</li>
              <li>‚Ä¢ Link up with portal team at the bridge</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="card border-l-4 border-theater-siege">
            <h4 class="font-display text-dnd-text mb-2">Theater 2: Juno Beach ‚Äî Move the Siege Engines</h4>
            <p class="text-dnd-text-muted text-sm mb-3">
              The siege train faces a brutal challenge: hauling massive catapults and trebuchets up the sandy
              bluffs of Hoc's Point and through difficult terrain while under fire.
            </p>
            <ul class="text-dnd-text-muted text-sm space-y-1">
              <li>‚Ä¢ Get creative ‚Äî winches, magic, brute force, or improvised solutions</li>
              <li>‚Ä¢ Protect the siege engines from saboteurs and enemy fire</li>
              <li>‚Ä¢ Reach the bridge before the window closes</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="card border-l-4 border-theater-portals">
            <h4 class="font-display text-dnd-text mb-2">Theater 3: Portals ‚Äî Disarm the Bridge</h4>
            <p class="text-dnd-text-muted text-sm mb-3">
              The portal team is already behind enemy lines ‚Äî the only force close enough to reach the bridge
              before the demolition order is given.
            </p>
            <ul class="text-dnd-text-muted text-sm space-y-1">
              <li>‚Ä¢ Assault the Duergar demolition platoon holding the bridge</li>
              <li>‚Ä¢ Neutralize sappers and disarm explosive charges</li>
              <li>‚Ä¢ Hold the bridge against counterattack until reinforced</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="card border-l-4 border-theater-air">
            <h4 class="font-display text-dnd-text mb-2">Theater 4: Air ‚Äî Block the Reinforcements</h4>
            <p class="text-dnd-text-muted text-sm mb-3">
              With air superiority achieved, flying units must land on the road beyond the bridge to intercept
              enemy reinforcements marching from the Coastal Keep.
            </p>
            <ul class="text-dnd-text-muted text-sm space-y-1">
              <li>‚Ä¢ Land on the inland road past the bridge</li>
              <li>‚Ä¢ Establish a blocking position against Keep reinforcements</li>
              <li>‚Ä¢ Buy time for the portal team and beach forces to secure the crossing</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="card bg-dnd-primary/10 border-dnd-primary">
          <p class="text-dnd-primary font-display text-center text-lg">
            The bridge must hold. The siege engines must cross. Everything depends on it.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Act IV -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-dnd-bg-secondary" id="act-4">
    <div class="container-custom">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-6">
          <span class="text-4xl">üî•</span>
          <div>
            <p class="section-title">Act IV</p>
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-display">The Fall of the Coastal Keep</h2>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="card mb-6">
          <p class="text-dnd-primary text-sm uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">The Final Battle</p>
          <p class="text-dnd-text-muted text-sm italic">Tone: Desperate, mythic, decisive</p>
        </div>

        <p class="text-dnd-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-8">
          All surviving forces converge on the Coastal Keep. The outcome of Act II determines how
          difficult this final battle will be.
        </p>

        <h3 class="font-display text-xl text-dnd-primary mb-4">The Twist: The Arcane Commander</h3>
        <div class="card border-dnd-secondary mb-6">
          <p class="text-dnd-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-4">
            The Keep is commanded by a <a href="/enemies" class="text-theater-portals hover:text-dnd-primary transition-colors font-semibold">Conclave Warmagus</a>, responsible for
            battlefield coordination, arcane relay with Athkatla, and synchronization of ground and air forces.
          </p>
          <p class="text-dnd-text-muted leading-relaxed">
            As the assault begins, the Warmagus reveals a final contingency...
          </p>
        </div>

        <h3 class="font-display text-xl text-dnd-primary mb-4">The Splintering of the Mind</h3>
        <p class="text-dnd-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-4">
          The Warmagus fractures into <strong class="text-dnd-text">four arcane aspects</strong>,
          each tied to a theater of war. Each splinter represents a facet of command:
        </p>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-4 mb-8">
          <div class="card text-center p-4">
            <span class="text-2xl block mb-2">üõ°Ô∏è</span>
            <p class="text-dnd-text text-sm font-display">Control</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card text-center p-4">
            <span class="text-2xl block mb-2">üí•</span>
            <p class="text-dnd-text text-sm font-display">Destruction</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card text-center p-4">
            <span class="text-2xl block mb-2">üé≠</span>
            <p class="text-dnd-text text-sm font-display">Deception</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card text-center p-4">
            <span class="text-2xl block mb-2">üëÅÔ∏è</span>
            <p class="text-dnd-text text-sm font-display">Dominion</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <p class="text-dnd-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-4">
          Each splinter manifests near or within one theater and must be defeated independently.
        </p>

        <div class="card bg-dnd-primary/10 border-dnd-primary">
          <p class="text-dnd-primary font-display text-center text-lg">
            Victory is collective.
          </p>
        </div>

        <h3 class="font-display text-xl text-dnd-primary mb-4 mt-8">The Final Moment</h3>
        <p class="text-dnd-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-4">
          Once all splinters ‚Äî or a decisive majority ‚Äî are destroyed:
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-dnd-text-muted ml-4 mb-6">
          <li>‚Ä¢ Arcane relays collapse</li>
          <li>‚Ä¢ Signal beacons fail</li>
          <li>‚Ä¢ Orders from Athkatla cease</li>
          <li>‚Ä¢ Enemy formations fragment</li>
        </ul>

        <p class="text-dnd-primary font-display text-xl text-center">
          The Iron Conclave has not been destroyed ‚Äî but its grip on Amn has been broken.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-dnd-bg-secondary">
    <div class="container-custom text-center">
      <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-display mb-4">
        <span class="gold-gradient">Ready to Join the Fight?</span>
      </h2>
      <p class="text-dnd-text-muted mb-8 max-w-xl mx-auto">
        Choose your theater and become part of this epic battle.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center justify-center gap-4">
        <a href="/signup" class="btn btn-primary">Sign Up Now</a>
        <a href="/theaters" class="btn btn-secondary">Explore Theaters</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
